==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Naphthol
<hw>Naph"thol</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Naphth</ets>alene + <ets>-ol</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>Any one of a series of hydroxyl derivatives of naphthalene,
analogous to phenol. In general they are crystalline substances with a
phenol (carbolic) odor.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><mcol><col><b>Naphthol blue</b></col>, <col><b>Naphthol
orange</b></col>, <col><b>Naphthol yellow</b></col></mcol>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld>, <cd>brilliant dyestuffs produced from certain
complex nitrogenous derivatives of naphthol or
naphthoquinone.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Naphthoquinone</ent>⟦br⟧
